                            <comment id="13846433" author="gzurowski" created="Thu, 12 Dec 2013 16:46:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch contains a new JUnit test &quot;JcrProducerSubNodeTest&quot; that creates a node and a sub node in the same node hierarchy. It will fail if the fix to JcrProducer (which is also part of the patch) is not applied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have also submitted a pull request for this fix: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/66&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/66&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13846587" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 12 Dec 2013 18:58:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch looks good. Only one checkstyle error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/Users/davsclaus/workspace/camel/components/camel-jcr/src/test/java/org/apache/camel/component/jcr/JcrProducerSubNodeTest.java:80: method call child at indentation level 16 not at correct indentation, 20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Details here how to build with checkstyle&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/building.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/building.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
